1
00:00:00,062 --> 00:00:02,836
Previously on Seducing Drake Palma

2
00:00:03,336 --> 00:00:04,104
What did you say?

3
00:00:04,129 --> 00:00:06,164
Make Drake Palma
your boyfriend!

4
00:00:09,175 --> 00:00:11,071
So how exactly are
you planning to pull off

5
00:00:11,095 --> 00:00:13,263
your- Mission Impossible:
Seducing Drake Palma?

6
00:00:13,525 --> 00:00:14,546
Hi, Drake!

7
00:00:17,475 --> 00:00:18,576
Hi, Drake!

8
00:00:18,601 --> 00:00:19,811
Psst! Psst!

9
00:00:20,016 --> 00:00:21,032
What?

10
00:00:23,523 --> 00:00:25,233
I’m just tying my shoelace.

11
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:26,401
Hi, Drake!

12
00:00:26,443 --> 00:00:27,819
I like you, Drake.

13
00:00:28,278 --> 00:00:29,946
Can you be my boyfriend?

14
00:00:31,114 --> 00:00:31,823
Okay.

15
00:00:31,865 --> 00:00:32,757
What the…

16
00:00:32,782 --> 00:00:33,758
Seriously?!

17
00:00:33,783 --> 00:00:34,788
That’s it?!

18
00:00:35,118 --> 00:00:36,126
We’re done.

19
00:00:37,871 --> 00:00:40,123
For all the girls who were hurt by Drake!

20
00:00:40,623 --> 00:00:41,626
Drake Palma!

21
00:00:42,834 --> 00:00:45,879
You’re my boyfriend now!

22
00:00:48,590 --> 00:00:49,649
Three…

23
00:00:49,674 --> 00:00:50,673
Two…

24
00:00:50,698 --> 00:00:51,176
One…

25
00:00:51,201 --> 00:00:52,220
We’re done!

26
00:00:53,928 --> 00:00:54,931
Bye!

27
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:11,352
Me?

28
00:01:15,075 --> 00:01:16,098
Drake, who is she?

29
00:01:57,325 --> 00:01:58,348
Hey!

30
00:01:58,952 --> 00:02:00,309
Why are you so happy today?

31
00:02:01,547 --> 00:02:02,566
Nothing.

32
00:02:02,789 --> 00:02:04,848
Why? Is it wrong
to be happy now?

33
00:02:05,601 --> 00:02:09,747
Ooh, I smell juicy gossip.

34
00:02:14,717 --> 00:02:16,028
So, what is it, bestie?

35
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:18,239
Spill it.

36
00:02:23,184 --> 00:02:24,196
What is it?

37
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:26,009
Promise, it stays between us.

38
00:02:26,312 --> 00:02:27,321
Promise.

39
00:02:27,814 --> 00:02:28,829
Come on, tell me.

40
00:02:32,735 --> 00:02:34,376
You’re being selfish now?

41
00:02:37,073 --> 00:02:38,095
Caught you!

42
00:02:39,617 --> 00:02:40,649
You’re annoying.

43
00:02:41,202 --> 00:02:43,138
Liar. You’re still trying to fake it.

44
00:02:43,163 --> 00:02:44,360
It’s not effective, girl!

45
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:46,040
It’s not working.

46
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:49,627
Try harder to convince me!

47
00:02:50,086 --> 00:02:51,254
If you won’t tell me,

48
00:02:51,254 --> 00:02:52,939
I’m going to hit you in the face with this.

49
00:02:52,964 --> 00:02:54,941
Wait, okay.

50
00:02:54,966 --> 00:02:56,013
Calm down, girl.

51
00:02:58,511 --> 00:03:00,763
This is what happened.

52
00:03:04,267 --> 00:03:05,466
I’m his girlfriend!

53
00:03:06,352 --> 00:03:07,380
Girlfriend?

54
00:03:07,857 --> 00:03:10,273
Oh, why does she
look so shocked?

55
00:03:10,899 --> 00:03:11,787
Actually—

56
00:03:12,066 --> 00:03:14,460
Yes! I’m really his girlfriend.

57
00:03:14,485 --> 00:03:15,695
As in girlfriend!

58
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:18,781
As in one word, girlfriend.

59
00:03:18,806 --> 00:03:20,099
We’re really a couple!

60
00:03:20,124 --> 00:03:21,990
Right? Right, Drakey baby?

61
00:03:27,391 --> 00:03:31,013
Oh no, what if he lets go of my hand
and pushes me away?

62
00:03:31,127 --> 00:03:32,560
That can’t happen!

63
00:03:37,114 --> 00:03:39,742
Wait, he didn’t push me?

64
00:03:40,386 --> 00:03:41,607
He’s improving!

65
00:03:42,472 --> 00:03:44,005
Really? What’s your name, dear?

66
00:03:44,474 --> 00:03:46,529
Oh, I’m Alys.

67
00:03:46,729 --> 00:03:50,038
Alys Zyril Perez,
soon to be Palma!

68
00:03:50,063 --> 00:03:51,091
Nice to meet you!

69
00:03:54,442 --> 00:03:56,318
This girl is so amusing.
Right, Katrina?

70
00:03:58,363 --> 00:04:00,657
Wow, she’s really pretty!

71
00:04:01,241 --> 00:04:03,091
Why don’t we all go inside?
Let’s have some snacks.

72
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:07,810
No, I really just came here to
tell you that I’m Drake’s girlfriend.

73
00:04:07,981 --> 00:04:09,013
How long have you been together?

74
00:04:11,584 --> 00:04:12,591
Five minutes?

75
00:04:15,171 --> 00:04:18,566
But I promise, Drake’s
dad, we’re going to last.

76
00:04:18,591 --> 00:04:19,607
Right, Drakey baby?

77
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:21,685
Really, Alys?

78
00:04:22,387 --> 00:04:24,614
But don’t call me “Drake‘s Dad”.

79
00:04:24,639 --> 00:04:25,779
It’s too long.

80
00:04:26,025 --> 00:04:28,152
Then what should I call you?

81
00:04:29,097 --> 00:04:30,888
Just call me “Uncle Steve.”

82
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:33,490
And she’s your Aunt Katrina, my fiancée.

83
00:04:34,190 --> 00:04:36,334
Hello, Uncle Steve, Aunt Katrina.

84
00:04:36,359 --> 00:04:37,771
Nice meeting you!

85
00:04:37,824 --> 00:04:39,092
I’m heading out now!

86
00:04:39,195 --> 00:04:40,802
Bye! Bye, Drakey baby!

87
00:04:51,249 --> 00:04:52,417
That was nerve-wracking!

88
00:04:53,751 --> 00:04:54,833
Drakey baby?

89
00:04:56,004 --> 00:04:57,088
You’re gross!

90
00:04:57,380 --> 00:04:58,372
Why do you care?

91
00:04:58,589 --> 00:04:59,677
It rhymes!

92
00:04:59,802 --> 00:05:01,052
- It’s cute!
- Whatever.

93
00:05:01,681 --> 00:05:02,794
So, why are you so happy?

94
00:05:06,806 --> 00:05:07,810
Why?

95
00:05:07,871 --> 00:05:09,607
You’re so slow!

96
00:05:10,042 --> 00:05:12,490
Because Drake is
my boyfriend now!

97
00:05:12,622 --> 00:05:13,855
Wow, delusional!

98
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:15,606
True! So ambitious, huh?

99
00:05:15,648 --> 00:05:17,066
As if Drake would go
for someone like her!

100
00:05:19,569 --> 00:05:21,435
Whatever with
these bitter girls!

101
00:05:21,571 --> 00:05:24,215
But for me, he’s
my boyfriend now.

102
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:25,435
He really is!

103
00:05:25,783 --> 00:05:27,458
Keep dreaming!
He’s going to break up with you!

104
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:29,512
No way!

105
00:05:29,537 --> 00:05:30,621
We’re legal.

106
00:05:30,646 --> 00:05:33,291
Uncle Steve will get
mad if he dumps me!

107
00:05:34,292 --> 00:05:35,184
Bestie...

108
00:05:35,209 --> 00:05:38,087
You’re insanely shameless - it’s epic!

109
00:05:38,497 --> 00:05:41,318
Whatever! What matters
is I finished my mission.

110
00:05:41,549 --> 00:05:43,526
Keep dreaming.
He’s going to dump you later!

111
00:05:43,551 --> 00:05:44,724
What if he doesn’t?

112
00:05:44,927 --> 00:05:47,113
Then I’ll teach you
how to read time.

113
00:05:47,138 --> 00:05:48,765
- Deal?
- Sure!

114
00:05:48,966 --> 00:05:50,725
- You’re buying me lunch, too.
- Deal.

115
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:54,794
Bestie...

116
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:56,939
Bestie, there he is.

117
00:06:01,444 --> 00:06:04,224
Oh no, please don’t
break up with me!

118
00:06:04,322 --> 00:06:05,423
Not now.

119
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:07,367
I don’t have money to treat Aya.

120
00:06:15,987 --> 00:06:17,738
Does he even sleep at home?

121
00:06:17,919 --> 00:06:21,672
He just got here and already
has his face buried in the desk.

122
00:06:22,131 --> 00:06:24,292
But the teacher doesn’t reprimand him.

123
00:06:24,317 --> 00:06:25,527
So unfair!

124
00:06:26,552 --> 00:06:28,532
But what’s even more unfair is

125
00:06:28,596 --> 00:06:31,949
if you don’t teach me how
to read time and buy me lunch.

126
00:06:31,997 --> 00:06:34,087
Because he didn’t
break up with me!

127
00:07:24,235 --> 00:07:27,822
I love you, Drake Palma!

128
00:07:31,163 --> 00:07:32,834
Thanks for the treat, bestie!

129
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:35,037
But take it easy with your sugar.

130
00:07:35,204 --> 00:07:36,414
It’s low sugar, okay.

131
00:07:37,707 --> 00:07:40,209
Hurry up and eat. I still need
to teach you how to read time.

132
00:07:40,535 --> 00:07:42,037
Chill. We’ve got plenty of time.

133
00:07:42,305 --> 00:07:44,536
It’s all your Drakey baby’s fault.

134
00:07:44,878 --> 00:07:46,713
He’s so unpredictable.

135
00:07:47,474 --> 00:07:49,976
I thought he never keeps a
girlfriend for long.

136
00:07:50,435 --> 00:07:52,312
Why didn’t he break up
with you right away?

137
00:07:53,682 --> 00:07:54,848
I lost my bet!

138
00:07:55,065 --> 00:07:56,066
It’s frustrating.

139
00:07:58,411 --> 00:07:59,543
Alys, look.

140
00:08:03,573 --> 00:08:05,598
- Yuck, Aya!
- Shut up!

141
00:08:05,623 --> 00:08:08,317
Look, Kei is following Drake!

142
00:08:09,537 --> 00:08:10,639
Oh my gosh!

143
00:08:10,788 --> 00:08:12,254
Kei’s really following Drake!

144
00:08:12,442 --> 00:08:13,543
Why, though?

145
00:08:13,925 --> 00:08:15,129
Come on, let’s follow them.

146
00:08:15,681 --> 00:08:19,278
What if this is the time she’ll push
with her dark plan to be with Drake?

147
00:08:19,857 --> 00:08:21,653
Oh no, that can’t happen!

148
00:08:23,067 --> 00:08:24,986
I can’t watch Sheen cry again.

149
00:08:25,303 --> 00:08:26,805
Come on, Aya!
Let’s go after them!

150
00:08:26,805 --> 00:08:27,825
Let’s go.

151
00:08:30,286 --> 00:08:31,451
Hey, Alys!

152
00:08:31,476 --> 00:08:33,536
Wait up! Hey!

153
00:08:33,561 --> 00:08:34,669
You’re so fast!

154
00:08:39,651 --> 00:08:40,986
Drake, I think we’re
a perfect match.

155
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:46,048
Bestie, can you lip-read
what Kei’s saying?

156
00:08:46,073 --> 00:08:47,383
I can’t understand.

157
00:08:47,409 --> 00:08:49,252
No one deserves you
in this campus...

158
00:08:49,953 --> 00:08:51,081
but me.

159
00:08:52,429 --> 00:08:55,455
Wait, it’s hard to read.

160
00:08:56,445 --> 00:08:57,799
I think she said,

161
00:08:59,086 --> 00:09:02,798
“Come on, Drake! I like you!”

162
00:09:03,976 --> 00:09:06,064
“Let’s be together!”

163
00:09:07,220 --> 00:09:11,216
Oh no, Aya! We
have to do something!

164
00:09:11,241 --> 00:09:12,492
You’re so overacting, bestie!

165
00:09:12,701 --> 00:09:14,290
You're overacting
too—with the slap!

166
00:09:14,315 --> 00:09:17,416
We’re not even sure
that’s what Kei said.

167
00:09:18,923 --> 00:09:21,861
What do you think? We
look good together, right?

168
00:09:22,296 --> 00:09:24,869
I can’t really read
Kei’s lips that well.

169
00:09:25,297 --> 00:09:28,697
She speaks so dramatically!

170
00:09:28,936 --> 00:09:30,759
You know what, I’ve got it.

171
00:09:30,839 --> 00:09:32,205
Come on, let’s go over there.

172
00:09:32,454 --> 00:09:34,705
- Ugh! What the heck!
- Oh no!

173
00:09:34,730 --> 00:09:35,822
Sheen my…

174
00:09:36,775 --> 00:09:38,213
What are you and Aya doing here?

175
00:09:40,072 --> 00:09:42,221
- We were just checking something.
- Yeah, just checking.

176
00:09:44,595 --> 00:09:45,971
Right?

177
00:09:53,183 --> 00:09:54,701
Sheen, come on.

178
00:09:54,866 --> 00:09:56,284
Let’s go to the classroom.

179
00:10:03,828 --> 00:10:07,955
Gosh, why are his
tears welling up again?

180
00:10:09,117 --> 00:10:12,400
So much for a man, Sheen.
You cry too much!

181
00:10:13,666 --> 00:10:16,400
Here, a hanky.

182
00:10:28,093 --> 00:10:30,839
Alys, it’s okay now.

183
00:10:31,384 --> 00:10:32,530
Sorry, Aya, okay?

184
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:33,985
I just love Kei so much.

185
00:10:34,921 --> 00:10:38,341
Sheen’s tears are
affecting me too much.

186
00:10:41,606 --> 00:10:42,540
Let’s go, Sheen!

187
00:10:42,577 --> 00:10:43,546
You stay here, Aya, okay?

188
00:10:43,571 --> 00:10:44,995
- Hey, where are you going?
- Let’s go, Sheen!

189
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:45,946
I’m coming too!

190
00:10:46,693 --> 00:10:47,837
Wait for me.

191
00:10:49,159 --> 00:10:51,328
Hold on. Sheen, I got you!

192
00:10:54,006 --> 00:10:55,556
What now, Sheen?

193
00:10:55,833 --> 00:10:57,165
Are you my stalker now?

194
00:10:57,973 --> 00:10:59,057
Excuse me, Kei.

195
00:10:59,222 --> 00:11:02,267
Sheen’s here because I’m
introducing her to my boyfriend.

196
00:11:02,502 --> 00:11:06,962
Drakey baby, this is
Sheen—my best friend!

197
00:11:09,426 --> 00:11:10,454
Sorry?

198
00:11:10,969 --> 00:11:12,153
You?

199
00:11:12,178 --> 00:11:13,446
Drake’s girlfriend?

200
00:11:17,524 --> 00:11:18,595
Keep dreaming.

201
00:11:19,246 --> 00:11:21,001
Hey! I’m your girlfriend, right?

202
00:11:22,677 --> 00:11:23,689
Ah...

203
00:11:26,837 --> 00:11:28,470
You heard that?

204
00:11:29,648 --> 00:11:31,962
He just said, “Ah…”

205
00:11:32,216 --> 00:11:33,999
“Ah” means “yes!”

206
00:11:34,024 --> 00:11:35,869
So, goodbye and good riddance!

207
00:11:35,869 --> 00:11:37,120
Oh Sheen, you were
about to leave right?

208
00:11:37,162 --> 00:11:38,515
Go ahead, tag along, Kei.

209
00:11:38,540 --> 00:11:40,937
Maybe you’re still
bitter about Drakey baby!

210
00:11:40,962 --> 00:11:43,101
Sheen’s right there too,
she’s bitter about you!

211
00:11:43,274 --> 00:11:44,415
Whatever!

212
00:11:51,261 --> 00:11:52,759
What are you looking at?

213
00:11:53,870 --> 00:11:56,399
I’m yelling at
him, but honestly,

214
00:11:56,737 --> 00:11:58,196
I’m scared!

215
00:11:58,449 --> 00:12:01,035
His stare is intense, promise!

216
00:12:01,583 --> 00:12:02,667
Tss.

217
00:12:09,652 --> 00:12:10,811
Hey, Drake.

218
00:12:10,836 --> 00:12:12,755
You’re only my boyfriend
in front of Sheen and Kei!

219
00:12:12,904 --> 00:12:13,939
Just in front of them!

220
00:12:14,515 --> 00:12:15,966
You think I like you?

221
00:12:16,162 --> 00:12:17,705
Dream on!

222
00:12:21,706 --> 00:12:23,346
Oh no!

223
00:12:26,294 --> 00:12:27,556
What to do?

224
00:12:27,786 --> 00:12:29,788
He looks mad about what I said.

225
00:12:31,348 --> 00:12:33,243
Keep dreaming. You’re ugly.

226
00:12:42,020 --> 00:12:44,321
Ugh, you’re so full of yourself!

227
00:12:49,067 --> 00:12:50,145
Keep dreaming.

228
00:12:50,170 --> 00:12:53,603
You’re ugly.

229
00:12:58,743 --> 00:13:00,119
Daddy…

230
00:13:00,958 --> 00:13:02,392
Mommy…

231
00:13:03,207 --> 00:13:06,462
Someone hurt your princess.

232
00:13:08,986 --> 00:13:10,681
He said I’m ugly.

233
00:13:12,276 --> 00:13:14,587
Which part? I’m gorgeous!

234
00:13:15,156 --> 00:13:16,908
I’m a Perez!

235
00:13:17,605 --> 00:13:21,345
There’s no ugly Perez.

236
00:13:24,317 --> 00:13:25,944
That Drake is so weird!

237
00:13:26,563 --> 00:13:27,705
Hey, ugly!

238
00:13:28,191 --> 00:13:29,211
You too!

239
00:13:30,295 --> 00:13:32,213
Hey...sorry.

240
00:13:33,005 --> 00:13:34,212
You’re not ugly.

241
00:13:35,976 --> 00:13:38,048
What happened earlier? Tell me.
What happened?

242
00:13:38,074 --> 00:13:40,021
I should be the one asking that.

243
00:13:40,046 --> 00:13:41,626
You’re the one who disappeared!

244
00:13:43,023 --> 00:13:45,845
Nature called, so I had to leave.

245
00:13:47,015 --> 00:13:49,048
And you and Sheen
were talking so long.

246
00:13:49,318 --> 00:13:51,779
I wonder what happened
with Sheen and Kei?

247
00:13:52,644 --> 00:13:54,104
Did they get back together?

248
00:13:56,508 --> 00:13:58,008
Oh no!

249
00:13:58,720 --> 00:13:59,929
I’m jealous!

250
00:13:59,954 --> 00:14:01,432
Ugh, I don’t want
to think about it!

251
00:14:02,717 --> 00:14:03,728
So dramatic!

252
00:14:04,772 --> 00:14:07,181
Bestie, come on, just tell me.

253
00:14:07,511 --> 00:14:09,187
Promise I won’t tell anyone.

254
00:14:09,212 --> 00:14:12,567
I won’t tell.
She’ll just laugh at me.

255
00:14:12,859 --> 00:14:13,878
Promise, I won’t tell.

256
00:14:13,903 --> 00:14:15,024
Never mind.

257
00:14:15,049 --> 00:14:16,296
I’m too lazy to tell you.

258
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:18,210
Alys, come on!

259
00:14:21,284 --> 00:14:23,752
We are not done yet,
Alys Zyril Perez!

260
00:14:23,786 --> 00:14:27,223
When a household,
or any business,

261
00:14:27,404 --> 00:14:30,310
have surplus cash,
or extra income,

262
00:14:30,335 --> 00:14:32,337
it falls down into what we were

263
00:14:32,362 --> 00:14:34,932
discussing and
studying last module two.

264
00:14:35,042 --> 00:14:36,094
Do you guys remember that?

265
00:14:36,119 --> 00:14:37,126
Oh my.

266
00:14:37,358 --> 00:14:40,403
I can’t even read the
numbers on the clock properly.

267
00:14:40,428 --> 00:14:41,571
I’m struggling!

268
00:14:41,596 --> 00:14:44,474
These are the entities

269
00:14:44,515 --> 00:14:46,559
that help move
that excess money!

270
00:14:46,601 --> 00:14:48,911
It’s very important
for you to understand,

271
00:14:48,936 --> 00:14:52,531
because this movement
gets the money where?

272
00:14:52,556 --> 00:14:55,657
To where it’s needed,
and where is that?

273
00:15:05,141 --> 00:15:07,352
Mr. Palma, why are you late?

274
00:15:08,017 --> 00:15:09,649
Good thing he woke up.

275
00:15:10,095 --> 00:15:11,712
You know what, just sit down.

276
00:15:18,025 --> 00:15:19,439
What the heck?

277
00:15:19,987 --> 00:15:22,485
When Drake doesn’t answer the teacher,
it’s totally fine?

278
00:15:23,179 --> 00:15:24,656
Is it because he’s a transferee?

279
00:15:24,954 --> 00:15:27,243
What if I transfer to a
different school, too?

280
00:15:27,517 --> 00:15:29,806
Am I allowed to sleep and be late, as well?

281
00:15:30,161 --> 00:15:33,831
Someday, I swear, I’m
reporting this to the principal.

282
00:15:35,358 --> 00:15:37,377
Where’s the equality?

283
00:15:37,402 --> 00:15:38,486
As I was saying,

284
00:15:39,355 --> 00:15:41,383
we will be putting
your learnings to a test.

285
00:15:42,532 --> 00:15:44,798
You know what the red box means?

286
00:15:47,845 --> 00:15:49,722
Quiz day! Twenty items!

287
00:15:57,024 --> 00:15:58,039
Good.

288
00:15:59,409 --> 00:16:00,484
Okay.

289
00:16:01,163 --> 00:16:03,320
Alright class, begin.

290
00:16:04,331 --> 00:16:07,292
Oh my God! This is so hard!

291
00:16:08,122 --> 00:16:11,242
I need to finish early
so I can go home!

292
00:16:12,271 --> 00:16:15,515
Why do we even need to study
Business Finance?

293
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:17,536
I don’t need this!

294
00:16:17,561 --> 00:16:19,469
All I need is basic arithmetic!

295
00:16:49,629 --> 00:16:50,928
Well, he works fast!

296
00:16:51,363 --> 00:16:53,914
It’s been less than ten minutes
since the test papers were handed.

297
00:16:55,971 --> 00:16:56,972
Class...

298
00:16:57,482 --> 00:17:01,444
If you’re like Mr. Palma,
we’d all be a lot happier.

299
00:17:01,861 --> 00:17:03,144
You can be late.

300
00:17:03,169 --> 00:17:04,297
You can sleep.

301
00:17:04,649 --> 00:17:07,443
Just make sure your
exams are perfect.

302
00:17:08,282 --> 00:17:09,351
You may leave.

303
00:17:12,288 --> 00:17:13,336
He’s lucky.

304
00:17:15,333 --> 00:17:17,079
Ugh, annoying!

305
00:17:18,002 --> 00:17:19,504
Show off.

306
00:17:25,176 --> 00:17:26,586
Fine, you're the genius!

307
00:17:59,314 --> 00:18:00,326
Huh?

308
00:18:02,045 --> 00:18:03,084
You may go.

309
00:18:06,968 --> 00:18:08,522
You cheated, didn’t you?

310
00:18:08,547 --> 00:18:10,061
- Let me just get my bag.
- You cheated.

311
00:18:16,523 --> 00:18:18,138
I’ll wait for you outside, okay?

312
00:18:18,971 --> 00:18:20,310
Annoying.

313
00:18:38,332 --> 00:18:39,810
Miss Perez...

314
00:18:39,835 --> 00:18:42,503
finished or not finished,
please pass your paper!

315
00:18:44,505 --> 00:18:46,424
Whew, finally!

316
00:18:47,343 --> 00:18:49,623
You’re probably the
last one to finish, Alys.

317
00:18:50,333 --> 00:18:52,420
You’re really a record holder.

318
00:18:52,945 --> 00:18:54,282
Well, sorry!

319
00:18:54,455 --> 00:18:55,998
Who told you to wait for me?

320
00:18:57,178 --> 00:18:59,865
Because I wanted to
ask what happened.

321
00:19:02,675 --> 00:19:03,740
Look at you!

322
00:19:04,354 --> 00:19:05,996
You’re the one who
didn’t want to spill the tea!

323
00:19:06,020 --> 00:19:07,480
What happened after I left?

324
00:19:11,036 --> 00:19:12,115
Alys!

325
00:19:18,718 --> 00:19:22,701
Well, it’s better than
seeing him always crying.

326
00:19:23,295 --> 00:19:26,248
Oh, my poor love life.

327
00:19:26,273 --> 00:19:27,547
Stop going after Sheen!

328
00:19:27,982 --> 00:19:30,317
He’s totally into Kei,
he won’t even notice you.

329
00:19:30,842 --> 00:19:33,490
And he doesn’t
like losers like you!

330
00:19:38,201 --> 00:19:41,162
What? I’m just
telling the truth!

331
00:19:41,491 --> 00:19:43,256
That’s what real friends do.

332
00:19:43,888 --> 00:19:45,318
They roast each other.

333
00:19:45,638 --> 00:19:47,974
So what now? Come on, spill it.

334
00:19:47,999 --> 00:19:49,670
Come on, do I really need to beg?

335
00:19:50,901 --> 00:19:52,232
So, this is what happened.

336
00:19:52,257 --> 00:19:54,403
Earlier in front of Kei,

337
00:19:54,428 --> 00:19:56,699
I introduced Sheen
and Drake to each other.

338
00:19:56,747 --> 00:19:58,631
I told them that Drake
is my boyfriend.

339
00:19:58,677 --> 00:20:00,239
Kei didn’t even believe it at first.

340
00:20:00,264 --> 00:20:02,116
But when Drake and I were left alone,

341
00:20:02,141 --> 00:20:03,904
I told him clearly that

342
00:20:04,138 --> 00:20:06,520
we’re only pretending to be a
couple in front of Sheen and Kei.

343
00:20:06,779 --> 00:20:10,131
Then I told him I’m
not even into him.

344
00:20:11,056 --> 00:20:12,724
- You know what he said to me?
- What?

345
00:20:12,999 --> 00:20:14,990
He said I was
delusional and ugly!

346
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:18,607
Drake actually said that?

347
00:20:19,684 --> 00:20:22,452
Wow! Drake has guts!

348
00:20:23,938 --> 00:20:25,456
What’s so funny about that?!

349
00:20:25,623 --> 00:20:27,141
He insulted your best friend!

350
00:20:27,166 --> 00:20:29,143
The nerve to call me ugly?

351
00:20:29,168 --> 00:20:30,895
Me? A Perez?

352
00:20:30,920 --> 00:20:32,303
There’s no ugly in our family!

353
00:20:32,328 --> 00:20:33,998
That Drake is so infuriating!

354
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:36,444
Sorry.

355
00:20:37,138 --> 00:20:41,701
It’s just that Drake barely talks and
that’s what he chooses to say.

356
00:20:41,726 --> 00:20:42,959
It’s kind of epic!

357
00:20:44,100 --> 00:20:45,231
Exactly!

358
00:20:45,256 --> 00:20:48,082
If that’s the only thing he’s gonna
say, he should’ve kept quiet.

359
00:20:48,107 --> 00:20:51,339
- So annoying!
- Oh, calm down, bestie.

360
00:20:51,913 --> 00:20:53,123
It’s just really epic.

361
00:20:53,148 --> 00:20:54,384
Stop it, seriously, stop!

362
00:20:54,424 --> 00:20:56,185
You’re ugly and delusional!

363
00:20:57,102 --> 00:20:58,294
Alys!

364
00:20:58,848 --> 00:21:00,324
Uncle Steve!

365
00:21:00,832 --> 00:21:02,803
- Hi!
- What are you doing here?

366
00:21:02,828 --> 00:21:04,261
I was just about to
have dinner with the family.

367
00:21:04,386 --> 00:21:06,590
And I saw you.
So, I parked to say hi.

368
00:21:06,615 --> 00:21:08,375
- Oh.
- Oh.

369
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,818
Drake’s in the car.

370
00:21:10,126 --> 00:21:12,388
He doesn’t want to get out.
You know how that kid is.

371
00:21:15,955 --> 00:21:19,537
I wonder what he and the beautiful
Aunt Katrina are talking about.

372
00:21:21,034 --> 00:21:22,243
Oh, is that so, Uncle?

373
00:21:22,268 --> 00:21:24,866
That’s okay, Drake’s
always been like that.

374
00:21:24,891 --> 00:21:26,621
You should’ve
introduced me, bestie.

375
00:21:26,646 --> 00:21:30,090
Oh, Uncle, by the way
this is Aya, my best friend.

376
00:21:30,115 --> 00:21:31,706
Hello, nice to
meet you, Uncle Steve!

377
00:21:31,731 --> 00:21:33,149
- Hi, Aya!
- Hello.

378
00:21:33,470 --> 00:21:35,810
You’re more handsome
than Drake. Legit.

379
00:21:37,261 --> 00:21:38,528
Thanks!

380
00:21:38,553 --> 00:21:40,395
Want to join us for dinner?

381
00:21:40,420 --> 00:21:41,161
Come with us.

382
00:21:41,186 --> 00:21:42,349
- Oh, yes!
- Oh no, it’s okay!

383
00:21:42,758 --> 00:21:44,744
Seriously, Aya!

384
00:21:45,182 --> 00:21:47,017
You just heard
“food” and jumped in!

385
00:21:47,747 --> 00:21:50,057
Yes! Let’s go, Uncle Steve!

386
00:21:50,082 --> 00:21:52,427
We’ll go ahead. Come
on let’s go, quick!

387
00:21:52,452 --> 00:21:53,553
That’s food!

388
00:21:56,568 --> 00:21:59,092
Hop in. I’ll take you
home at eight, don’t worry.

389
00:21:59,117 --> 00:22:01,310
- Okay, Uncle. No problem.
- Okay, Uncle.

390
00:22:05,513 --> 00:22:07,199
You go first, bestie!

391
00:22:07,224 --> 00:22:08,242
Quick, quick!

392
00:22:08,267 --> 00:22:09,762
Go on!

393
00:22:09,794 --> 00:22:11,426
Fine, I’m going! Wait!

394
00:22:11,462 --> 00:22:14,215
- Hurry, scoot over!
- Wait!

395
00:22:15,178 --> 00:22:16,388
There!

396
00:22:34,298 --> 00:22:36,185
Why did I even come along?

397
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:39,758
Are we broke now that I have
to crash someone else’s dinner?

398
00:22:39,783 --> 00:22:41,162
This is all Aya’s fault!

399
00:22:59,848 --> 00:23:04,406
Look at Drake and Aunt Katrina
staring at each other. Hmmm.

400
00:23:04,602 --> 00:23:05,687
Fishy?

401
00:23:09,068 --> 00:23:11,973
Oh no, they’re both staring at each other.

402
00:23:26,994 --> 00:23:28,316
Wow!

403
00:23:29,315 --> 00:23:30,608
Honey, let’s eat!

404
00:23:31,113 --> 00:23:32,940
Everything looks so good!

405
00:23:32,965 --> 00:23:35,378
I’m eating some of
these for the first time!

406
00:23:35,403 --> 00:23:36,863
Aya, what are you doing?

407
00:23:37,489 --> 00:23:39,649
This is your first and last,
bestie, okay?

408
00:23:39,817 --> 00:23:42,065
Look, you almost
finished everything!

409
00:23:42,090 --> 00:23:44,465
You’re exaggerating,
I’ve barely eaten.

410
00:23:44,871 --> 00:23:46,706
Good thing Uncle Steve is nice!

411
00:23:46,731 --> 00:23:49,293
It’s okay. If it’s not
enough, we’ll order more.

412
00:23:49,754 --> 00:23:51,453
- Oh—
- Really?

413
00:23:51,809 --> 00:23:54,236
Uncle, it’s okay.
This is more than enough, thank you.

414
00:23:54,261 --> 00:23:57,324
- Come on, Alys.
- Right, Aya? Right?

415
00:23:58,719 --> 00:24:00,096
Botejyu is so good.

416
00:24:00,655 --> 00:24:01,922
You really like food, huh?

417
00:24:02,214 --> 00:24:05,276
We own several restaurant
franchises abroad.

418
00:24:05,301 --> 00:24:07,573
- Wow!
- Wow! Really?

419
00:24:07,598 --> 00:24:10,704
Maybe we can get a free
meal sometime, Uncle Steve?

420
00:24:10,729 --> 00:24:12,147
Oh my god, Aya!

421
00:24:12,915 --> 00:24:14,613
What? It’s free food!

422
00:24:16,020 --> 00:24:18,096
By the way, I’m curious.

423
00:24:18,121 --> 00:24:19,801
What happened to Drake’s mom?

424
00:24:20,396 --> 00:24:21,399
Bestie!

425
00:24:21,712 --> 00:24:23,271
Why are you asking
so many questions?

426
00:24:23,296 --> 00:24:24,769
It’s embarrassing.

427
00:24:24,794 --> 00:24:26,402
Why not? I’m just curious.

428
00:24:27,031 --> 00:24:28,408
If you don’t mind.

429
00:24:28,433 --> 00:24:30,201
It’s okay, no problem.

430
00:24:30,529 --> 00:24:33,707
Drake’s okay with it,
so it’s fine by me.

431
00:24:34,700 --> 00:24:38,981
Drake was around twelve or
thirteen when his mom died.

432
00:24:41,512 --> 00:24:43,035
Then I met Katrina.

433
00:24:44,280 --> 00:24:47,965
Now she’s about to
become part of our family.

434
00:24:51,914 --> 00:24:53,362
Oh.

435
00:24:53,387 --> 00:24:55,207
- Bestie.
- Oops, I dropped it, sorry.

436
00:25:00,845 --> 00:25:01,863
Ouch!

437
00:25:02,716 --> 00:25:04,208
Is there a problem?

438
00:25:04,593 --> 00:25:07,387
No...nothing.

439
00:25:08,113 --> 00:25:09,733
Everything’s delicious!

440
00:25:09,758 --> 00:25:12,285
We’re really enjoying
the food. It’s super good.

441
00:25:29,676 --> 00:25:30,754
Alys!

442
00:25:31,463 --> 00:25:32,547
- Mom!
- Come here!

443
00:25:36,875 --> 00:25:38,310
Hi, mom.

444
00:25:38,553 --> 00:25:39,721
Where have you been?

445
00:25:40,129 --> 00:25:42,339
Aya and I
just finished a project.

446
00:25:43,285 --> 00:25:44,840
We needed to get it done.

447
00:25:45,294 --> 00:25:47,944
Oh please! Maybe you
just have a new boyfriend?

448
00:25:48,079 --> 00:25:49,414
Dad!

449
00:25:49,602 --> 00:25:51,496
You just don’t want
to bring him here.

450
00:25:51,667 --> 00:25:52,737
I don’t like him--

451
00:25:53,350 --> 00:25:56,557
I mean, I’m not ready to
have a boyfriend right now.

452
00:25:56,582 --> 00:25:58,709
You know, it would be a
distraction from my studies.

453
00:25:59,565 --> 00:26:01,567
Alys, it’s okay to
have a boyfriend.

454
00:26:01,967 --> 00:26:03,473
Think of it as an inspiration.

455
00:26:03,993 --> 00:26:05,660
Don’t take it too
seriously, okay?

456
00:26:06,065 --> 00:26:08,238
That’s right. Just have fun.

457
00:26:08,445 --> 00:26:10,884
But don’t forget
your studies, alright?

458
00:26:11,048 --> 00:26:12,135
Just chill.

459
00:26:12,348 --> 00:26:13,934
Yes, mom. Just chill.

460
00:26:14,832 --> 00:26:18,402
Oh, by the way, your brother
called earlier from the US.

461
00:26:18,744 --> 00:26:20,535
He said he couldn’t reach you.

462
00:26:21,116 --> 00:26:22,832
Seems like he’s
having fun over there.

463
00:26:23,358 --> 00:26:25,398
I really miss that crazy guy.

464
00:26:25,423 --> 00:26:26,731
That’s probably
why he’s been tex—

465
00:26:31,013 --> 00:26:32,400
What?!

466
00:26:32,433 --> 00:26:33,598
What is it, Alys?

467
00:26:34,181 --> 00:26:35,262
Is something wrong?

468
00:26:35,808 --> 00:26:37,065
Nothing.

469
00:26:37,097 --> 00:26:38,098
I’m chill.

470
00:26:39,426 --> 00:26:41,918
I’m just chill. Okay, bye!

471
00:26:59,482 --> 00:27:01,270
What happened to your face?

472
00:27:02,300 --> 00:27:04,231
Why are you even asking?

473
00:27:04,334 --> 00:27:07,128
You were sending
random texts last night.

474
00:27:08,236 --> 00:27:10,738
Because I saw it myself!

475
00:27:11,723 --> 00:27:12,905
Oops.

476
00:27:13,215 --> 00:27:14,777
- Bestie...
- It fell, sorry.

477
00:27:23,186 --> 00:27:24,223
Ouch.

478
00:27:26,763 --> 00:27:28,887
I’m really sleepy.

479
00:27:31,220 --> 00:27:32,524
Sorry.

480
00:27:32,549 --> 00:27:34,049
It was a juicy gossip.

481
00:27:34,082 --> 00:27:37,294
You needed to know because
we’re partners in crime, right?

482
00:27:39,239 --> 00:27:40,340
So, what now?

483
00:27:43,561 --> 00:27:44,904
Come on, bestie!

484
00:27:44,929 --> 00:27:46,472
Ouch, what’s your problem?

485
00:27:46,731 --> 00:27:50,301
Aren’t you curious
why they were holding hands?

486
00:27:50,985 --> 00:27:54,864
If I know, Aunt Katrina
is a cradle snatcher.

487
00:27:55,156 --> 00:27:57,700
Gross.

488
00:27:57,700 --> 00:27:59,368
I won’t call her Aunt Katrina.

489
00:27:59,368 --> 00:28:02,738
Just Katrina because
she doesn’t deserve my respect.

490
00:28:03,247 --> 00:28:05,458
So what if there’s something
between her and Drake?

491
00:28:05,913 --> 00:28:06,918
Duh?

492
00:28:07,918 --> 00:28:10,707
Wow, Alys, I didn’t
know you were like this.

493
00:28:11,297 --> 00:28:14,425
After everything Uncle Steve
has shown you kindness,

494
00:28:14,467 --> 00:28:15,765
you’ll let him be fooled,

495
00:28:15,790 --> 00:28:17,417
even though you know
you can do something?

496
00:28:19,792 --> 00:28:21,866
You’re making me
feel guilty, bestie.

497
00:28:21,891 --> 00:28:23,809
Do you want me to be a spy?

498
00:28:23,934 --> 00:28:25,816
Exactly, bestie! You got it!

499
00:28:27,104 --> 00:28:28,205
Are you serious?

500
00:28:28,253 --> 00:28:29,613
I’m just kidding.

501
00:28:29,940 --> 00:28:32,715
You always want me to do
the weirdest things.

502
00:28:33,194 --> 00:28:36,322
Bestie, do it for Uncle Steve.

503
00:28:37,198 --> 00:28:38,356
Whatever!

504
00:28:38,783 --> 00:28:40,993
All I want to do now is sleep.

505
00:28:41,285 --> 00:28:42,613
So let me sleep!

506
00:28:44,824 --> 00:28:47,628
I’m already stressing
about Sheen my loves,

507
00:28:47,653 --> 00:28:51,128
now you want me to deal with
this Drake–Katrina thing, too?

508
00:28:51,153 --> 00:28:52,438
But…

509
00:28:52,463 --> 00:28:53,839
What if it’s true?

510
00:28:54,320 --> 00:28:56,800
Poor Uncle Steve.

511
00:28:56,900 --> 00:28:58,949
This is Aya’s fault.

512
00:28:59,237 --> 00:29:01,449
Now my conscience
is eating away at me!

513
00:29:05,851 --> 00:29:09,332
This weirdo here
can sleep like a log.

514
00:29:12,291 --> 00:29:14,126
I wish I could sleep too—

515
00:29:14,151 --> 00:29:15,878
if only I wasn’t
thinking about that weird

516
00:29:15,903 --> 00:29:17,863
and shady something
with Aunt Katrina!

517
00:29:24,352 --> 00:29:28,324
Seek the truth. Tell the truth.
Live the truth.

518
00:29:28,707 --> 00:29:29,730
Aya!

519
00:29:33,420 --> 00:29:36,632
For today, class,
you’ll work in pairs.

520
00:29:36,632 --> 00:29:41,379
It’s up to you, class, what
you want to make.

521
00:29:41,404 --> 00:29:44,972
As long as the ingredients are
available in the Home Eco room.

522
00:29:44,997 --> 00:29:45,998
Alright?

523
00:29:46,267 --> 00:29:47,560
- Yes, ma’am!
- Yes, ma’am!

524
00:29:47,781 --> 00:29:49,160
There!

525
00:29:49,418 --> 00:29:51,785
Good thing we have an activity today!

526
00:29:52,064 --> 00:29:53,582
This will keep me awake.

527
00:29:53,927 --> 00:29:55,846
I really love this subject.

528
00:29:56,018 --> 00:29:58,675
Avery Clyde Balasbas.

529
00:29:59,572 --> 00:30:01,740
Danielle D. Marchan

530
00:30:01,949 --> 00:30:03,683
with Xander King.

531
00:30:03,740 --> 00:30:06,925
Mohaira Sanama
with Arvic Roy Manalo.

532
00:30:06,950 --> 00:30:10,800
Aliyah Cassandra Dedel.
Herbert Harold Lacsi.

533
00:30:11,052 --> 00:30:14,264
Duna Duncan, Gabriel Lago

534
00:30:15,399 --> 00:30:19,695
and Gabriella Pineda
with Albert De Joya.

535
00:30:19,720 --> 00:30:23,266
Lord, please.
Not in my favorite subject.

536
00:30:23,304 --> 00:30:26,066
Perez, Alys Zyril...

537
00:30:26,307 --> 00:30:31,437
Palma, Drake Sebastian.

538
00:30:31,437 --> 00:30:32,730
What?!

539
00:30:36,816 --> 00:30:40,066
Baking is my stress reliever.

540
00:30:41,100 --> 00:30:43,519
I forgot all my problems—

541
00:30:43,784 --> 00:30:45,824
my love for Sheen,

542
00:30:46,378 --> 00:30:51,761
and the fishy relationship
between Drake and Aunt Katrina.

543
00:30:53,168 --> 00:30:55,419
For now, I’ll bake first.

544
00:30:56,387 --> 00:30:59,949
Let’s go, Alys Zyril Perez.
You can do it, aja!

545
00:31:08,469 --> 00:31:11,558
Class, just to reiterate...

546
00:31:12,437 --> 00:31:16,215
You’ll stay in pairs and
make identical products

547
00:31:16,240 --> 00:31:18,824
using the ingredients available.

548
00:31:19,861 --> 00:31:25,700
Consistency in appearance
and quality is very important.

549
00:31:26,972 --> 00:31:30,647
I’ll be in the faculty room
if you need me, okay?

550
00:31:30,672 --> 00:31:34,676
- Yes, ma’am!
- Move! Move! Move!

551
00:31:34,676 --> 00:31:35,691
Yes, ma’am.

552
00:31:42,558 --> 00:31:43,723
So...

553
00:31:44,036 --> 00:31:45,412
Should I go up to him?

554
00:31:46,479 --> 00:31:49,855
Of all people, why did I have
to be partnered with him?

555
00:31:50,430 --> 00:31:56,380
If I approach him, I’d be tempted
to ask him about Aunt Katrina.

556
00:31:56,752 --> 00:31:58,621
I was born a gossip!

557
00:31:59,325 --> 00:32:02,428
No, forget it.
If he doesn’t want to help,

558
00:32:02,585 --> 00:32:04,337
I’ll just report him to Ma’am.

559
00:33:15,985 --> 00:33:17,236
- Alys!
- Yeah?

560
00:33:17,278 --> 00:33:18,921
You’re taking forever.
I’ll go ahead, okay?

561
00:33:18,946 --> 00:33:19,655
- Go ahead, bestie!
- Love you!

562
00:33:19,655 --> 00:33:20,364
Bye! Take care!

563
00:33:20,364 --> 00:33:22,769
- Aja!
- Aja!

564
00:33:24,895 --> 00:33:25,912
Oh my God.

565
00:33:25,937 --> 00:33:27,264
Tada!

566
00:33:27,747 --> 00:33:30,629
This turned out so pretty.
A total masterpiece.

567
00:33:31,584 --> 00:33:32,621
I’m bringing this home.

568
00:33:33,085 --> 00:33:34,462
I’m so proud of myself.

569
00:33:41,135 --> 00:33:42,488
Where’s that weirdo?

570
00:33:43,710 --> 00:33:45,238
He’s probably asleep again.

571
00:33:45,723 --> 00:33:46,848
Oh well, I don’t care.

572
00:33:47,892 --> 00:33:48,918
What time is it?

573
00:33:55,441 --> 00:33:56,535
I can’t read this!

574
00:33:57,443 --> 00:33:58,488
I don’t know with myself.

575
00:34:00,822 --> 00:34:03,049
It’s only four-thirty.

576
00:34:03,074 --> 00:34:04,512
I can still shower.

577
00:34:18,161 --> 00:34:23,666
Hi, mom!
I’ll bring you cake.

578
00:34:24,246 --> 00:34:25,340
How are you?

579
00:34:32,816 --> 00:34:33,846
Really?

580
00:34:33,871 --> 00:34:35,088
Sure, that sounds good.

581
00:34:35,113 --> 00:34:36,364
Take care, dear!

582
00:34:46,450 --> 00:34:47,473
Oh.

583
00:34:51,289 --> 00:34:53,965
I need to get this checked by
Ma’am first, then I can go home.

584
00:34:59,005 --> 00:35:00,043
Who’s that?

585
00:35:06,304 --> 00:35:07,246
No way.

586
00:35:07,847 --> 00:35:10,004
Drake? Baking a cake?

587
00:35:20,019 --> 00:35:21,284
What’s your problem?

588
00:35:22,231 --> 00:35:26,629
Well, you’re doing the wrong thing.

589
00:35:32,504 --> 00:35:33,715
Whatever.

590
00:35:35,769 --> 00:35:37,385
Hey, why are you taking my cake?!

591
00:35:37,410 --> 00:35:39,395
- Give it to me.
- Are you serious?!

592
00:35:39,629 --> 00:35:41,151
This is mine!
I’m bringing it home!

593
00:35:41,176 --> 00:35:42,924
This is mine.
Just make another one!

594
00:35:42,949 --> 00:35:44,425
No way, this is mine!

595
00:35:44,425 --> 00:35:46,558
- It’s mine now!
- No, it’s mine!

596
00:35:54,618 --> 00:35:56,982
My cake!

597
00:35:57,007 --> 00:35:59,485
My cake!

598
00:35:59,510 --> 00:36:01,816
Why did you leave me?!

599
00:36:12,648 --> 00:36:16,318
Why did you leave me?!

600
00:36:16,788 --> 00:36:18,373
Mmm. Mmm.

601
00:36:18,935 --> 00:36:20,553
What am I supposed
to do with that?!

602
00:36:20,578 --> 00:36:21,621
Stare at it!

603
00:36:23,798 --> 00:36:24,801
Tss.

604
00:36:30,945 --> 00:36:32,321
Hey, Drake Palma!

605
00:36:32,574 --> 00:36:35,129
Don’t turn your back
on me while I’m talking!

606
00:36:35,851 --> 00:36:38,660
You ruined my cake,
so help me replace it!

607
00:36:39,490 --> 00:36:40,496
Tss.

608
00:36:42,256 --> 00:36:43,331
Annoying.

609
00:36:45,920 --> 00:36:47,494
Annoying your face!

610
00:36:47,519 --> 00:36:50,121
You ruined my cake, so you’re
helping me make a new one!

611
00:36:50,146 --> 00:36:52,066
Whether you like it
or you like it!

612
00:36:52,576 --> 00:36:55,121
I already told mom
I was bringing her cake!

613
00:37:00,053 --> 00:37:02,316
There. You're smart, right?

614
00:37:09,040 --> 00:37:10,777
Mmm, you got this!

615
00:37:15,583 --> 00:37:17,980
Fine, whatever!
Just copy what I’m doing.

616
00:37:30,293 --> 00:37:32,308
Not like that—like this.

617
00:37:32,988 --> 00:37:34,129
There you go.

618
00:37:46,270 --> 00:37:47,410
What now?

619
00:37:47,559 --> 00:37:49,176
You’ve got flour on your face.

620
00:37:53,178 --> 00:37:54,989
So grumpy.

621
00:37:55,014 --> 00:37:56,276
Oh my gosh...

622
00:37:56,301 --> 00:37:58,348
Is there anyone
colder than this guy?

623
00:38:01,965 --> 00:38:04,055
- Ouch!
- What now?

624
00:38:04,080 --> 00:38:05,518
Oh, sorry.

625
00:38:05,543 --> 00:38:07,527
I didn’t mean to.

626
00:38:25,137 --> 00:38:27,002
Hey, Drake. Are you done?

627
00:38:27,027 --> 00:38:28,121
Let me see!

628
00:38:29,248 --> 00:38:30,293
So grumpy.

629
00:38:32,652 --> 00:38:34,070
Help me clean up,

630
00:38:34,095 --> 00:38:36,167
before we get this
checked by Ma’am.

631
00:38:36,192 --> 00:38:37,860
We’ll lose points if
we don’t clean up.

632
00:38:43,770 --> 00:38:45,824
I can’t believe he left me
to clean up.

633
00:38:47,083 --> 00:38:49,933
You’re so annoying.
Seriously, so annoying!

634
00:38:52,174 --> 00:38:53,832
So annoying!

635
00:38:57,289 --> 00:38:59,230
Good thing you guys caught up!

636
00:38:59,453 --> 00:39:02,957
Why did it take you so
long to bake your cake?!

637
00:39:05,237 --> 00:39:06,238
This is your fault!

638
00:39:18,547 --> 00:39:20,988
Why do your
cakes look different?

639
00:39:21,320 --> 00:39:23,051
We didn’t do it in pairs.

640
00:39:31,235 --> 00:39:32,254
Hey!

641
00:39:33,419 --> 00:39:34,566
Drake Palma!

642
00:39:37,139 --> 00:39:38,551
Good thing you’re still here!

643
00:39:40,462 --> 00:39:41,926
You’re really something, aren’t you?

644
00:39:42,430 --> 00:39:44,222
You’re the one who didn’t help,

645
00:39:44,247 --> 00:39:46,015
you’re the one who ruined my cake,

646
00:39:46,047 --> 00:39:48,042
you’re the one I taught how to bake,

647
00:39:48,067 --> 00:39:51,715
you’re the one who didn't help
in cleaning up the kitchen,

648
00:39:52,610 --> 00:39:54,987
Yet you're the one
who got a higher grade than me.

649
00:39:55,098 --> 00:39:57,715
Because you told Ma’am
that we didn’t work in pairs?!

650
00:39:58,251 --> 00:39:59,590
Where’s the justice in that?!

651
00:40:15,325 --> 00:40:16,441
Are you done?

652
00:40:18,077 --> 00:40:19,918
What are you smiling about?

653
00:40:21,258 --> 00:40:22,269
Bye.

654
00:40:35,354 --> 00:40:36,613
Who was he texting?

655
00:40:44,305 --> 00:40:45,535
Oh gosh...

656
00:40:46,232 --> 00:40:48,495
Being a gossip is hard work—

657
00:40:48,676 --> 00:40:50,371
I’m becoming like Aya.

658
00:40:59,494 --> 00:41:00,512
No.

659
00:41:00,908 --> 00:41:02,259
This is not gossiping.

660
00:41:02,612 --> 00:41:04,489
This is truth-finding.

661
00:41:05,286 --> 00:41:06,660
Data gathering mode.

662
00:41:31,123 --> 00:41:32,224
You know what Drake,

663
00:41:32,249 --> 00:41:34,207
you’d be lucky if I
became your girlfriend.

664
00:41:35,074 --> 00:41:36,316
There’s only one of me.

665
00:41:37,143 --> 00:41:38,862
We’re the same in every way—

666
00:41:38,887 --> 00:41:41,282
rich, smart, good-looking.

667
00:41:41,323 --> 00:41:42,457
I’m not available.

668
00:41:43,598 --> 00:41:45,959
Huh? I thought—

669
00:41:45,984 --> 00:41:47,082
I like someone else.

670
00:42:05,923 --> 00:42:09,151
On the next episode of
Seducing Drake Palma.

671
00:42:09,176 --> 00:42:10,566
You’re burning up.

672
00:42:11,908 --> 00:42:13,004
Drake.

673
00:42:13,366 --> 00:42:14,543
You have a fever.

674
00:42:16,150 --> 00:42:17,710
You’re not a pervert.

675
00:42:18,066 --> 00:42:20,730
You’re just a concerned citizen.

676
00:42:21,384 --> 00:42:22,465
Oh, pervert!

677
00:42:28,857 --> 00:42:30,004
Bestie, let’s go home

678
00:42:31,740 --> 00:42:33,418
Look at that.

679
00:42:33,915 --> 00:42:36,113
Your tutor is Drake.

680
00:42:36,712 --> 00:42:37,463
Unbelievable.

681
00:42:37,463 --> 00:42:39,027
You’re destined to be together.

682
00:42:39,590 --> 00:42:40,854
What do you want?

683
00:42:40,879 --> 00:42:42,377
We have to go
somewhere, hurry!

684
00:42:42,402 --> 00:42:45,082
I told Uncle Steve that
we’ll go to their house.

685
00:42:45,351 --> 00:42:46,027
Huh?

686
00:42:46,052 --> 00:42:47,457
By the way,

687
00:42:47,482 --> 00:42:50,466
don’t you ever dare
seduce Drake during your tutorials,

688
00:42:50,491 --> 00:42:51,504
okay?

689
00:42:52,144 --> 00:42:53,270
Excuse me.

690
00:42:54,236 --> 00:42:56,410
Why would I have
to seduce Drake Palma?

691
00:42:57,036 --> 00:42:58,620
He’s already my boyfriend.

692
00:43:01,574 --> 00:43:02,716
Boyfriend?

693
00:43:03,355 --> 00:43:05,137
Do you think I’ll believe that?
